essary generic struct","url":"https://viruta.org/reducing-binary-size-generics.html","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vzmwvx/reducing_code_size_librsvg_by_removing","submitter_user":{"username":"calvin","created_at":"2014-07-01T06:47:13.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Soon we will all have special names... names designed to make the cathode ray tube resonate.\r\n\r\nDavid Chisnall stan account.","is_moderator":false,"karma":95625,"avatar_url":"/avatars/calvin-100.png","invited_by_user":"nbyouri","github_username":"NattyNarwhal"},"tags":["performance","rust"]},{"short_id":"nnd0hf","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nnd0hf","created_at":"2023-03-02T22:08:37.000-06:00","title":"Rethinking splice()","url":"https://lwn.net/Articles/923237/","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nnd0hf/rethinking_splice","submitter_user":{"username":"jmillikin","created_at":"2021-07-22T09:39:26.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Currently semi-retired; formerly at Google (2011-2017) and Stripe (2017-2022)","is_moderator":false,"karma":1116,"avatar_url":"/avatars/jmillikin-100.png","invited_by_user":"pushcx"},"tags":["linux"]},{"short_id":"vhp170","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vhp170","created_at":"2023-03-02T05:49:57.000-06:00","title":"OpenPGP / GnuPG notepad recommendations?","url":"","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":15,"description":"\u003cp\u003eCan the community recommend some trusted, secure, open-source, easy-to-use notepad-like editors that can encrypt / decrypt the text with GnuPG out of the box?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor my own use-cases I have my own scripts that tie \u003ccode\u003egpg\u003c/code\u003e with my favorite editor, but I‚Äôm looking for a simple to use editor (like LeafPad, MousePad, Howl, etc.) that given a file-path (which is either an \u003ccode\u003e.gpg\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e.asc\u003c/code\u003e file) will transparently decrypt it, allow the user to view / edit it, and upon closing to just re-encrypt that file keeping the recipients intact (and perhaps signing it).  (It doesn‚Äôt matter if its for the terminal or X.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôve found many password managers that rely on GnuPG, and I bet there are plugins for the various \u003ccode\u003evi\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eemacs\u003c/code\u003e clones out there, but so far nothing sensible on this other front‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eP.S.  I‚Äôm starting to suspect that the whole OpenPGP ecosystem was built with only one use-case in mind:  encrypted and/or signed email.  The rest, although technically possible, suffers from a complete lack of actually usable tools‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eP.P.S:  No, \u003ccode\u003eage\u003c/code\u003e doesn‚Äôt solve this problem either.  It just replaces one set of cryptographic primitives with another, but on the usability front I would say it‚Äôs even a bit worse than GnuPG for normal people‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Can the community recommend some trusted, secure, open-source, easy-to-use notepad-like editors that can encrypt / decrypt the text with GnuPG out of the box?\r\n\r\nFor my own use-cases I have my own scripts that tie `gpg` with my favorite editor, but I'm looking for a simple to use editor (like LeafPad, MousePad, Howl, etc.) that given a file-path (which is either an `.gpg` or `.asc` file) will transparently decrypt it, allow the user to view / edit it, and upon closing to just re-encrypt that file keeping the recipients intact (and perhaps signing it).  (It doesn't matter if its for the terminal or X.)\r\n\r\nI've found many password managers that rely on GnuPG, and I bet there are plugins for the various `vi` and `emacs` clones out there, but so far nothing sensible on this other front...\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nP.S.  I'm starting to suspect that the whole OpenPGP ecosystem was built with only one use-case in mind:  encrypted and/or signed email.  The rest, although technically possible, suffers from a complete lack of actually usable tools...\r\n\r\nP.P.S:  No, `age` doesn't solve this problem either.  It just replaces one set of cryptographic primitives with another, but on the usability front I would say it's even a bit worse than GnuPG for normal people...","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vhp170/openpgp_gnupg_notepad_recommendations","submitter_user":{"username":"ciprian_craciun","created_at":"2022-02-14T13:47:43.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"IT enthusiast, from programming to operating systems, from networking to cryptography, from cloud to hardware, from Erlang to Java.","is_moderator":false,"karma":813,"avatar_url":"/avatars/ciprian_craciun-100.png","invited_by_user":"syn-ack"},"tags":["ask","cryptography"]},{"short_id":"0ibswc","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/0ibswc","created_at":"2023-03-01T11:33:55.000-06:00","title":"Gleam v0.27 - Hello panic, goodbye try","url":"https://gleam.run/news/v0.27-hello-panic-goodbye-try/","score":46,"flags":1,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/0ibswc/gleam_v0_27_hello_panic_goodbye_try","submitter_user":{"username":"lpil","created_at":"2019-04-02T03:50:42.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"","is_moderator":false,"karma":1408,"avatar_url":"/avatars/lpil-100.png","invited_by_user":"djm","github_username":"lpil"},"tags":["erlang","plt","release"]},{"short_id":"4gk4db","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4gk4db","created_at":"2023-03-01T14:13:38.000-06:00","title":"Godot 4.0 sets sail","url":"https://godotengine.org/article/godot-4-0-sets-sail/","score":62,"flags":0,"comment_count":7,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4gk4db/godot_4_0_sets_sail","submitter_user":{"username":"bkhl","created_at":"2021-12-15T16:17:18.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"","is_moderator":false